mous theoretical pronouncements on poetry, including his remarks on “negative capability” and “the truth of Imagination”—cannot be fully understood without understanding the religious context in which they were made.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / English, Irish, Scottish, Welsh.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311074975540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780691265001?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780691265001423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780691265001/original  a978-3-11-074975-5  Princeton University Press Complete eBook-Package 2024b2024  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles